Installation procedure for Duro on Linux/POSIX systems
======================================================

Duro uses SCons (www.scons.org) to build itself. Type:

scons
tests/all.tcl (optional)
scons install

To compile Duro, you need GNU Libtool, Berkeley DB 4.3,
and Tcl 8.1 or later.

Depending on the system, it may be necessary to use link Duro applications
with libpthread.



Berkeley DB is assumed to be located in /usr/local/BerkeleyDB.4.4.
If Berkeley DB is located in a different directory, ...

To build Duro without Tcl support, ...
Note that since most tests depend on Durotcl, running the tests will not
be possible in this case. Duroadmin and Durodump will not be available either.
